Fetching the system directly from PDB using pymol¶

In [3]:
cmd.fetch(code='1AZ8',type='pdb1',path='test/')
cmd.select(name='Prot',selection='polymer.protein')
cmd.select(name='Lig',selection='organic')
cmd.save(filename='test/1AZ8_clean.pdb',format='pdb',selection='Prot')
cmd.save(filename='test/1AZ8_lig.mol2',format='mol2',selection='Lig')
cmd.delete('all')

Docking¶

In [12]:
v = Vina(sf_name='vina')

v.set_receptor('test/1AZ8_clean_H.pdbqt')

v.set_ligand_from_file('test/1AZ8_lig_H.pdbqt')

v.compute_vina_maps(center=[box_center['center_x'], box_center['center_y'], box_center['center_z']], 
                    box_size=[box_size['size_x'], box_size['size_y'], box_size['size_z']])

'''
# Score the current pose
energy = v.score()
print('Score before minimization: %.3f (kcal/mol)' % energy[0])

# Minimized locally the current pose
energy_minimized = v.optimize()
print('Score after minimization : %.3f (kcal/mol)' % energy_minimized[0])
v.write_pose('1AZ8_ligand_minimized.pdbqt', overwrite=True)
'''

# Dock the ligand
v.dock(exhaustiveness=8, n_poses=5)
v.write_poses('test/1AZ8_ligand_vina_out.pdbqt', n_poses=5, overwrite=True)

Docking results conversion from pdbqt to sdf¶

In [13]:
results = [m for m in pybel.readfile(filename='test/1AZ8_ligand_vina_out.pdbqt',format='pdbqt')]
out=pybel.Outputfile(filename='test/1AZ8_ligand_vina_out.sdf',format='sdf',overwrite=True)
for pose in results:
    pose.addh()
    out.write(pose)
out.close()

# load protein
prot = mda.Universe("test/1AZ8_clean_H.pdb",guess_bonds=True)
prot = plf.Molecule.from_mda(prot)
prot.n_residues

# load ligands
path = str('test/1AZ8_ligand_vina_out.sdf')
lig_suppl = list(plf.sdf_supplier(path))
# generate fingerprint
fp = plf.Fingerprint()
fp.run_from_iterable(lig_suppl, prot)
results_df = fp.to_dataframe(return_atoms=True)
results_df
